description: Crystal River Boat Builders is an educational organization whose mission is to encourage and promulgate the study, construction, and use of traditional small craft as a vehicle to explore the history and heritage of the Florida Gulf Coast. We hope to expand our efforts by instituting a community boat building program. Position Description: The Boat Building Instructor will aid members of the CRBB in our heritage boat building projects. The instructor will also take charge of a community boat building project. In that role the instructor will design such a program and coordinate its operation. The program might involve running parent and child boat building sessions over a number of days, classes for novice wood workers, and perhaps an apprentice program for youth to work alongside our members. The program might involve running adult and child boat building sessions over a number of days, classes for novice wood workers, and perhaps an apprentice program for youth work alongside our members. Leadership of the program requires woodworking and boat building experience as well as the ability to relate to youth of all backgrounds. Successful applicants will be able to demonstrate a commitment to engaging young people through project-based learning. Work schedules will be determined by the programs and projects that the Instructor initiates.
